title: Temperature of HDDs Using S.M.A.R.T via SCSI
agents: linux
catalog: os/hardware
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the temperature of hard disk drives using the information reported by
 S.M.A.R.T. This configured via the `Temperature` rule.

 The check requires enabling agent {smart_posix}.
 Moreover, the monitored device needs support the SCSI protocol.

item:
 Block device name, e.g., /dev/da0

discovery:
 One service is created if the device uses the SCSI protocol.
